100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On September 14, 1925, the League of Nations convened a conference in Geneva to address ongoing disputes in Eastern Europe, reflecting the post-World War I tensions. In the United States, the debate over Prohibition intensified as various states reported rising crime rates linked to bootlegging. Meanwhile, in the realm of science, a groundbreaking discovery in the field of bacteriology was announced, promising advancements in public health measures.
